The Problem with Newtonian Physics Maybe we're all just one big moment one big maw of raw potential and endless probabilities piercing the eyelids and heading straight towards the cerebral cortex in hopes of finding something down there in the dark dank basement of the psyche. Yeah...that must be it something, somewhere --I can feel it in my quarks. Its that shudder/goose bump thing you do when the toes curl up and I hear you howl at the moon like a dog. And maybe this time, time isn't the answer for we both know that time never resolved any disassociate train of thought and time never made anything better especially not for us. From mechanics to fractals, from icecream to god where the blind passion can both kill and concieve in a single brush stroke of the young artists hands. Emerging, submerging, illusively still just one moment where I can love you, undress you, hold you, make you mine just one second where we can transcend this skin and become one with the skies just one moment where we can be for now, and then, and ever still just one second please.

aerosol cans ripe to rot
flutter motionless explosion
lemon scented palmolive spring.

Viable they kill themself
giving insides for defectives
splitting clitoris they watched
until almost circular in rotation
(and I couldn't help the blood)

Recanting one aorta at a time
cubicals they sang rusted harmonies
punctuated by the need for infection
and the disease for which they shook

Spoonfed his viscera
incisors clattered into lips
quivers in exploited anticipation
they strung corpses 
in the street.

Enamel in discourse
never knowing their drip
and I marvel at the diameter 
of your succulent spit.

Normalacy is and has never been any issue of consequence. Any person with minimal perceptional skills can comprehend that a sense of normalacy is subjective cognitive functioning in societies that embodies the ones sense of stability NOT actual external conditions of what is. Now granted we never have spoken in person but that does not change the fact that I do not like you. Your political agendas against your fellow man aswell as your own bias against me led me to this conclusion. Objectivity cannot exist in this world, any great writer should know this. One can only describe their perceptions of reality, not actual reality. Read up on Immanuel Kant and the Das Ding an Sich idea, you'll find him quite informative in your quest for profound insight. While one may argue that what is written by their hand does not capture the essence of their selfhood (which I would argree with full-heartedly) you must understand that one is written does in some manner convey a part of you. For example: I cannot say that the poetry I write fully captures the essence of what I am because I believe that I am an infinitively complex organism, incapable of being confined to paper, ink, and obscure mental references. I cannot say however, that what I have written did not come from me and is not linked to my being in some way. What makes what I write unique is that I wrote it and no one has a perspective on the universe like I do. My physical form as well as my socialization is unique to mankind and the history of mankind and there has to be a bit of someone in what they create or it wouldn't be theirs.... I guess what I'm trying to say is that I'm glad you've gone back to sports because you suck at life... :)

Have you ever considered that there is no real "purpose" in life? Do you honestly think you're parents gave that much thought into having you or maybe you are just the result of one unrestrained night of dispropotional barebacking? If you still are clinging to the notion of true happiness you're bound to live a miserable existence because nobody is happy all the time because that would make them miserable. People aren't ment to experience just one emotion all the time, the entire spectrum from happy to sad, from caring to apathatic, even manipulative to niave is inside you every moment, all the time and its you that lets them out. Finding yourself is not (and has never been) an issue of ones external conditions. While most of ones personality is formed due to their surroundings, understanding what you are is something that happens within you. Once you know you are you can become at peace with your surroundings regardless of how menacing they may be. The one thing that I know to be constant is that people leave, (they die, they move, they just stop talking to you, etc). While this may not be liked it is inevitable. Instead of dwelling on social interactions that are no longer in place why don't you develop new ones? Yes, I know that no two friendships (or even mutanies) are the same but if you dwell on what you lost then you will miss out on so much more by pushing away what could have been. Never forget that this entire world is full of possibilites and none of them you pick is ever wrong. Also learn to exist independantly from people, learn who you are in relation to yourself at first and then see who you are around others, they are almost always two different people(ie. do you think you could masturbate in front of a group of your friends?) By the way, get rid of that I'm fucked up bullshit because nobody thinks its attractive and frankly its goddamn annoying.
